  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Vulnerable Malian Refugees and Selected Host Communities through Livelihood Opportunities and Protection Activities in the North Region, Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following intercommunal violence in Mali and in Burkina Faso, Malian refugees, host communities and internally displaced persons (IDPs) are coexisting in the northern region of Burkina Faso. In response, this project aims at supporting 4900 vulnerable Malian refugees, IDPs and community members by working on strengthening their economic security and community cohesion through livelihood opportunities. The project also focuses on strengthening those communities&apos; protection needs through psychosocial and gender-based violence support activities, as well as the provision of emergency shelters for 100 most-at-risk beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
